91bool ValidateStreamParams(const StreamParams& sp) {
92 if (sp.ssrcs.empty()) {
93 RTC_DLOG(LS_ERROR) << "No SSRCs in stream parameters: " << sp.ToString();
94 return false;
95 }
96 if (sp.ssrcs.size() > 1) {
97 RTC_DLOG(LS_ERROR) << "Multiple SSRCs in stream parameters: "
98 << sp.ToString();
99 return false;
100 }
101 return true;
102}
103
104// Dumps an AudioCodec in RFC 2327-ish format.
105std::string ToString(const AudioCodec& codec) {
106 rtc::StringBuilder ss;
107 ss << codec.name << "/" << codec.clockrate << "/" << codec.channels;
108 if (!codec.params.empty()) {
109 ss << " {";
110 for (const auto& param : codec.params) {
111 ss << " " << param.first << "=" << param.second;
112 }
113 ss << " }";
114 }
115 ss << " (" << codec.id << ")";
116 return ss.Release();
117}
118
119bool IsCodec(const AudioCodec& codec, const char* ref_name) {
120 return absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(codec.name, ref_name);
121}
122
123bool FindCodec(const std::vector<AudioCodec>& codecs,
124 const AudioCodec& codec,
125 AudioCodec* found_codec) {
126 for (const AudioCodec& c : codecs) {
127 if (c.Matches(codec)) {
128 if (found_codec != NULL) {
129 *found_codec = c;
130 }
131 return true;
132 }
133 }
134 return false;
135}
136
137bool VerifyUniquePayloadTypes(const std::vector<AudioCodec>& codecs) {
138 if (codecs.empty()) {
139 return true;
140 }
141 std::vector<int> payload_types;
142 absl::c_transform(codecs, std::back_inserter(payload_types),
143 [](const AudioCodec& codec) { return codec.id; });
144 absl::c_sort(payload_types);
145 return absl::c_adjacent_find(payload_types) == payload_types.end();
146}

148absl::optional<std::string> GetAudioNetworkAdaptorConfig(
149 const AudioOptions& options) {
150 if (options.audio_network_adaptor && *options.audio_network_adaptor &&
151 options.audio_network_adaptor_config) {
152 // Turn on audio network adaptor only when |options_.audio_network_adaptor|
153 // equals true and |options_.audio_network_adaptor_config| has a value.
154 return options.audio_network_adaptor_config;
155 }
156 return absl::nullopt;
157}

159// Returns its smallest positive argument. If neither argument is positive,
160// returns an arbitrary nonpositive value.
161int MinPositive(int a, int b) {
162 if (a <= 0) {
163 return b;
164 }
165 if (b <= 0) {
166 return a;
167 }
168 return std::min(a, b);
169}
170
171// |max_send_bitrate_bps| is the bitrate from "b=" in SDP.
172// |rtp_max_bitrate_bps| is the bitrate from RtpSender::SetParameters.
173absl::optional<int> ComputeSendBitrate(int max_send_bitrate_bps,
174 absl::optional<int> rtp_max_bitrate_bps,
175 const webrtc::AudioCodecSpec& spec) {
176 // If application-configured bitrate is set, take minimum of that and SDP
177 // bitrate.
178 const int bps = rtp_max_bitrate_bps
179 ? MinPositive(max_send_bitrate_bps, *rtp_max_bitrate_bps)
180 : max_send_bitrate_bps;
181 if (bps <= 0) {
182 return spec.info.default_bitrate_bps;
183 }
184
185 if (bps < spec.info.min_bitrate_bps) {
186 // If codec is not multi-rate and |bps| is less than the fixed bitrate then
187 // fail. If codec is not multi-rate and |bps| exceeds or equal the fixed
188 // bitrate then ignore.
189 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to set codec " << spec.format.name
190 << " to bitrate " << bps
191 << " bps"
192 ", requires at least "
193 << spec.info.min_bitrate_bps << " bps.";
194 return absl::nullopt;
195 }
196
197 if (spec.info.HasFixedBitrate()) {
198 return spec.info.default_bitrate_bps;
199 } else {
200 // If codec is multi-rate then just set the bitrate.
201 return std::min(bps, spec.info.max_bitrate_bps);
202 }
203}

205bool IsEnabled(const webrtc::WebRtcKeyValueConfig& config,
206 absl::string_view trial) {
207 return absl::StartsWith(config.Lookup(trial), "Enabled");

210struct AdaptivePtimeConfig {
211 bool enabled = false;
212 webrtc::DataRate min_payload_bitrate = webrtc::DataRate::KilobitsPerSec(16);
213 // Value is chosen to ensure FEC can be encoded, see LBRR_WB_MIN_RATE_BPS in
214 // libopus.
215 webrtc::DataRate min_encoder_bitrate = webrtc::DataRate::KilobitsPerSec(16);
216 bool use_slow_adaptation = true;
217
218 absl::optional<std::string> audio_network_adaptor_config;
219
220 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::StructParametersParser> Parser() {
221 return webrtc::StructParametersParser::Create( //
222 "enabled", &enabled, //
223 "min_payload_bitrate", &min_payload_bitrate, //
224 "min_encoder_bitrate", &min_encoder_bitrate, //
225 "use_slow_adaptation", &use_slow_adaptation);
226 }
227
228 explicit AdaptivePtimeConfig(const webrtc::WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials) {
229 Parser()->Parse(trials.Lookup("WebRTC-Audio-AdaptivePtime"));
230#if WEBRTC_ENABLE_PROTOBUF
231 webrtc::audio_network_adaptor::config::ControllerManager config;
232 auto* frame_length_controller =
233 config.add_controllers()->mutable_frame_length_controller_v2();
234 frame_length_controller->set_min_payload_bitrate_bps(
235 min_payload_bitrate.bps());
236 frame_length_controller->set_use_slow_adaptation(use_slow_adaptation);
237 config.add_controllers()->mutable_bitrate_controller();
238 audio_network_adaptor_config = config.SerializeAsString();
239#endif
240 }
241};

245WebRtcVoiceEngine::WebRtcVoiceEngine(
246 webrtc::TaskQueueFactory* task_queue_factory,
247 webrtc::AudioDeviceModule* adm,
248 const rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioEncoderFactory>& encoder_factory,
249 const rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioDecoderFactory>& decoder_factory,
250 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioMixer> audio_mixer,
251 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::AudioProcessing> audio_processing,
252 webrtc::AudioFrameProcessor* audio_frame_processor,
253 const webrtc::WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials)
254 : task_queue_factory_(task_queue_factory),
255 adm_(adm),
256 encoder_factory_(encoder_factory),
257 decoder_factory_(decoder_factory),
258 audio_mixer_(audio_mixer),
259 apm_(audio_processing),
260 audio_frame_processor_(audio_frame_processor),
261 audio_red_for_opus_trial_enabled_(
262 IsEnabled(trials, "WebRTC-Audio-Red-For-Opus")),
263 minimized_remsampling_on_mobile_trial_enabled_(
264 IsEnabled(trials, "WebRTC-Audio-MinimizeResamplingOnMobile")) {
265 // This may be called from any thread, so detach thread checkers.
266 worker_thread_checker_.Detach();
267 signal_thread_checker_.Detach();
268 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "WebRtcVoiceEngine::WebRtcVoiceEngine";
269 RTC_DCHECK(decoder_factory);
270 RTC_DCHECK(encoder_factory);
271 // The rest of our initialization will happen in Init.
272}
273
274WebRtcVoiceEngine::~WebRtcVoiceEngine() {
275 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
276 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "WebRtcVoiceEngine::~WebRtcVoiceEngine";
277 if (initialized_) {
278 StopAecDump();
279
280 // Stop AudioDevice.
281 adm()->StopPlayout();
282 adm()->StopRecording();
283 adm()->RegisterAudioCallback(nullptr);
284 adm()->Terminate();
285 }
286}

288void WebRtcVoiceEngine::Init() {
289 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
290 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "WebRtcVoiceEngine::Init";
291
292 // TaskQueue expects to be created/destroyed on the same thread.
293 low_priority_worker_queue_.reset(
294 new rtc::TaskQueue(task_queue_factory_->CreateTaskQueue(
295 "rtc-low-prio", webrtc::TaskQueueFactory::Priority::LOW)));
296
297 // Load our audio codec lists.
298 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "Supported send codecs in order of preference:";
299 send_codecs_ = CollectCodecs(encoder_factory_->GetSupportedEncoders());
300 for (const AudioCodec& codec : send_codecs_) {
301 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << ToString(codec);
302 }
303
304 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "Supported recv codecs in order of preference:";
305 recv_codecs_ = CollectCodecs(decoder_factory_->GetSupportedDecoders());
306 for (const AudioCodec& codec : recv_codecs_) {
307 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << ToString(codec);
308 }
309
310#if defined(WEBRTC_INCLUDE_INTERNAL_AUDIO_DEVICE)
311 // No ADM supplied? Create a default one.
312 if (!adm_) {
313 adm_ = webrtc::AudioDeviceModule::Create(
314 webrtc::AudioDeviceModule::kPlatformDefaultAudio, task_queue_factory_);
315 }
316#endif // WEBRTC_INCLUDE_INTERNAL_AUDIO_DEVICE
317 RTC_CHECK(adm());
318 webrtc::adm_helpers::Init(adm());
319
320 // Set up AudioState.
321 {
322 webrtc::AudioState::Config config;
323 if (audio_mixer_) {
324 config.audio_mixer = audio_mixer_;
325 } else {
326 config.audio_mixer = webrtc::AudioMixerImpl::Create();
327 }
328 config.audio_processing = apm_;
329 config.audio_device_module = adm_;
330 if (audio_frame_processor_)
331 config.async_audio_processing_factory =
332 rtc::make_ref_counted<webrtc::AsyncAudioProcessing::Factory>(
333 *audio_frame_processor_, *task_queue_factory_);
334 audio_state_ = webrtc::AudioState::Create(config);
335 }
336
337 // Connect the ADM to our audio path.
338 adm()->RegisterAudioCallback(audio_state()->audio_transport());
339
340 // Set default engine options.
341 {
342 AudioOptions options;
343 options.echo_cancellation = true;
344 options.auto_gain_control = true;
345#if defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
346 // On iOS, VPIO provides built-in NS.
347 options.noise_suppression = false;
348 options.typing_detection = false;
349#else
350 options.noise_suppression = true;
351 options.typing_detection = true;
352#endif
353 options.experimental_ns = false;
354 options.highpass_filter = true;
355 options.stereo_swapping = false;
356 options.audio_jitter_buffer_max_packets = 200;
357 options.audio_jitter_buffer_fast_accelerate = false;
358 options.audio_jitter_buffer_min_delay_ms = 0;
359 options.audio_jitter_buffer_enable_rtx_handling = false;
360 options.experimental_agc = false;
361 options.residual_echo_detector = true;
362 bool error = ApplyOptions(options);
363 RTC_DCHECK(error);
364 }
365 initialized_ = true;
366}

370 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);

384bool WebRtcVoiceEngine::ApplyOptions(const AudioOptions& options_in) {
385 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
386 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "WebRtcVoiceEngine::ApplyOptions: "
387 << options_in.ToString();
388 AudioOptions options = options_in; // The options are modified below.
389
390 // Set and adjust echo canceller options.
391 // Use desktop AEC by default, when not using hardware AEC.
392 bool use_mobile_software_aec = false;
393
394#if defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
395 if (options.ios_force_software_aec_HACK &&
396 *options.ios_force_software_aec_HACK) {
397 // EC may be forced on for a device known to have non-functioning platform
398 // AEC.
399 options.echo_cancellation = true;
400 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
401 << "Force software AEC on iOS. May conflict with platform AEC.";
402 } else {
403 // On iOS, VPIO provides built-in EC.
404 options.echo_cancellation = false;
405 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Always disable AEC on iOS. Use built-in instead.";
406 }
407#elif defined(WEBRTC_ANDROID)
408 use_mobile_software_aec = true;
409#endif
410
411// Override noise suppression options for Android.
412#if defined(WEBRTC_ANDROID)
413 options.typing_detection = false;
414 options.experimental_ns = false;
415#endif
416
417// Set and adjust gain control options.
418#if defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
419 // On iOS, VPIO provides built-in AGC.
420 options.auto_gain_control = false;
421 options.experimental_agc = false;
422 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Always disable AGC on iOS. Use built-in instead.";
423#elif defined(WEBRTC_ANDROID)
424 options.experimental_agc = false;
425#endif
426
427#if defined(WEBRTC_IOS) || defined(WEBRTC_ANDROID)
428 // Turn off the gain control if specified by the field trial.
429 // The purpose of the field trial is to reduce the amount of resampling
430 // performed inside the audio processing module on mobile platforms by
431 // whenever possible turning off the fixed AGC mode and the high-pass filter.
432 // (https://bugs.chromium.org/p/webrtc/issues/detail?id=6181).
433 if (minimized_remsampling_on_mobile_trial_enabled_) {
434 options.auto_gain_control = false;
435 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Disable AGC according to field trial.";
436 if (!(options.noise_suppression.value_or(false) ||
437 options.echo_cancellation.value_or(false))) {
438 // If possible, turn off the high-pass filter.
439 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
440 << "Disable high-pass filter in response to field trial.";
441 options.highpass_filter = false;
442 }
443 }
444#endif
445
446 if (options.echo_cancellation) {
447 // Check if platform supports built-in EC. Currently only supported on
448 // Android and in combination with Java based audio layer.
449 // TODO(henrika): investigate possibility to support built-in EC also
450 // in combination with Open SL ES audio.
451 const bool built_in_aec = adm()->BuiltInAECIsAvailable();
452 if (built_in_aec) {
453 // Built-in EC exists on this device. Enable/Disable it according to the
454 // echo_cancellation audio option.
455 const bool enable_built_in_aec = *options.echo_cancellation;
456 if (adm()->EnableBuiltInAEC(enable_built_in_aec) == 0 &&
457 enable_built_in_aec) {
458 // Disable internal software EC if built-in EC is enabled,
459 // i.e., replace the software EC with the built-in EC.
460 options.echo_cancellation = false;
461 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
462 << "Disabling EC since built-in EC will be used instead";
463 }
464 }
465 }
466
467 if (options.auto_gain_control) {
468 bool built_in_agc_avaliable = adm()->BuiltInAGCIsAvailable();
469 if (built_in_agc_avaliable) {
470 if (adm()->EnableBuiltInAGC(*options.auto_gain_control) == 0 &&
471 *options.auto_gain_control) {
472 // Disable internal software AGC if built-in AGC is enabled,
473 // i.e., replace the software AGC with the built-in AGC.
474 options.auto_gain_control = false;
475 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
476 << "Disabling AGC since built-in AGC will be used instead";
477 }
478 }
479 }
480
481 if (options.noise_suppression) {
482 if (adm()->BuiltInNSIsAvailable()) {
483 bool builtin_ns = *options.noise_suppression;
484 if (adm()->EnableBuiltInNS(builtin_ns) == 0 && builtin_ns) {
485 // Disable internal software NS if built-in NS is enabled,
486 // i.e., replace the software NS with the built-in NS.
487 options.noise_suppression = false;
488 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
489 << "Disabling NS since built-in NS will be used instead";
490 }
491 }
492 }
493
494 if (options.stereo_swapping) {
495 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Stereo swapping enabled? " << *options.stereo_swapping;
496 audio_state()->SetStereoChannelSwapping(*options.stereo_swapping);
497 }
498
499 if (options.audio_jitter_buffer_max_packets) {
500 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "NetEq capacity is "
501 << *options.audio_jitter_buffer_max_packets;
502 audio_jitter_buffer_max_packets_ =
503 std::max(20, *options.audio_jitter_buffer_max_packets);
504 }
505 if (options.audio_jitter_buffer_fast_accelerate) {
506 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "NetEq fast mode? "
507 << *options.audio_jitter_buffer_fast_accelerate;
508 audio_jitter_buffer_fast_accelerate_ =
509 *options.audio_jitter_buffer_fast_accelerate;
510 }
511 if (options.audio_jitter_buffer_min_delay_ms) {
512 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "NetEq minimum delay is "
513 << *options.audio_jitter_buffer_min_delay_ms;
514 audio_jitter_buffer_min_delay_ms_ =
515 *options.audio_jitter_buffer_min_delay_ms;
516 }
517 if (options.audio_jitter_buffer_enable_rtx_handling) {
518 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "NetEq handle reordered packets? "
519 << *options.audio_jitter_buffer_enable_rtx_handling;
520 audio_jitter_buffer_enable_rtx_handling_ =
521 *options.audio_jitter_buffer_enable_rtx_handling;
522 }
523
524 webrtc::AudioProcessing* ap = apm();
525 if (!ap) {
526 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
527 << "No audio processing module present. No software-provided effects "
528 "(AEC, NS, AGC, ...) are activated";
529 return true;
530 }
531
532 webrtc::Config config;
533
534 if (options.experimental_ns) {
535 experimental_ns_ = options.experimental_ns;
536 }
537 if (experimental_ns_) {
538 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Experimental ns is enabled? " << *experimental_ns_;
539 config.Set<webrtc::ExperimentalNs>(
540 new webrtc::ExperimentalNs(*experimental_ns_));
541 }
542
543 webrtc::AudioProcessing::Config apm_config = ap->GetConfig();
544
545 if (options.echo_cancellation) {
546 apm_config.echo_canceller.enabled = *options.echo_cancellation;
547 apm_config.echo_canceller.mobile_mode = use_mobile_software_aec;
548 }
549
550 if (options.auto_gain_control) {
551 const bool enabled = *options.auto_gain_control;
552 apm_config.gain_controller1.enabled = enabled;
553#if defined(WEBRTC_IOS) || defined(WEBRTC_ANDROID)
554 apm_config.gain_controller1.mode =
555 apm_config.gain_controller1.kFixedDigital;
556#else
557 apm_config.gain_controller1.mode =
558 apm_config.gain_controller1.kAdaptiveAnalog;
559#endif
560 constexpr int kMinVolumeLevel = 0;
561 constexpr int kMaxVolumeLevel = 255;
562 apm_config.gain_controller1.analog_level_minimum = kMinVolumeLevel;
563 apm_config.gain_controller1.analog_level_maximum = kMaxVolumeLevel;
564 }
565 if (options.tx_agc_target_dbov) {
566 apm_config.gain_controller1.target_level_dbfs = *options.tx_agc_target_dbov;
567 }
568 if (options.tx_agc_digital_compression_gain) {
569 apm_config.gain_controller1.compression_gain_db =
570 *options.tx_agc_digital_compression_gain;
571 }
572 if (options.tx_agc_limiter) {
573 apm_config.gain_controller1.enable_limiter = *options.tx_agc_limiter;
574 }
575
576 if (options.highpass_filter) {
577 apm_config.high_pass_filter.enabled = *options.highpass_filter;
578 }
579
580 if (options.residual_echo_detector) {
581 apm_config.residual_echo_detector.enabled = *options.residual_echo_detector;
582 }
583
584 if (options.noise_suppression) {
585 const bool enabled = *options.noise_suppression;
586 apm_config.noise_suppression.enabled = enabled;
587 apm_config.noise_suppression.level =
588 webrtc::AudioProcessing::Config::NoiseSuppression::Level::kHigh;
589 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "NS set to " << enabled;
590 }
591
592 if (options.typing_detection) {
593 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Typing detection is enabled? "
594 << *options.typing_detection;
595 apm_config.voice_detection.enabled = *options.typing_detection;
596 }
597
598 ap->ApplyConfig(apm_config);
599 return true;
600}

612std::vector<webrtc::RtpHeaderExtensionCapability>
613WebRtcVoiceEngine::GetRtpHeaderExtensions() const {
614 RTC_DCHECK(signal_thread_checker_.IsCurrent());
615 std::vector<webrtc::RtpHeaderExtensionCapability> result;
616 int id = 1;
617 for (const auto& uri :
618 {webrtc::RtpExtension::kAudioLevelUri,
619 webrtc::RtpExtension::kAbsSendTimeUri,
620 webrtc::RtpExtension::kTransportSequenceNumberUri,
621 webrtc::RtpExtension::kMidUri, webrtc::RtpExtension::kRidUri,
622 webrtc::RtpExtension::kRepairedRidUri}) {
623 result.emplace_back(uri, id++, webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirection::kSendRecv);
624 }
625 return result;
626}

671
672std::vector<AudioCodec> WebRtcVoiceEngine::CollectCodecs(
673 const std::vector<webrtc::AudioCodecSpec>& specs) const {
674 PayloadTypeMapper mapper;
675 std::vector<AudioCodec> out;
676
677 // Only generate CN payload types for these clockrates:
678 std::map<int, bool, std::greater<int>> generate_cn = {
679 {8000, false}, {16000, false}, {32000, false}};
680 // Only generate telephone-event payload types for these clockrates:
681 std::map<int, bool, std::greater<int>> generate_dtmf = {
682 {8000, false}, {16000, false}, {32000, false}, {48000, false}};
683
684 auto map_format = [&mapper](const webrtc::SdpAudioFormat& format,
685 std::vector<AudioCodec>* out) {
686 absl::optional<AudioCodec> opt_codec = mapper.ToAudioCodec(format);
687 if (opt_codec) {
688 if (out) {
689 out->push_back(*opt_codec);
690 }
691 } else {
692 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Unable to assign payload type to format: "
693 << rtc::ToString(format);
694 }
695
696 return opt_codec;
697 };
698
699 for (const auto& spec : specs) {
700 // We need to do some extra stuff before adding the main codecs to out.
701 absl::optional<AudioCodec> opt_codec = map_format(spec.format, nullptr);
702 if (opt_codec) {
703 AudioCodec& codec = *opt_codec;
704 if (spec.info.supports_network_adaption) {
705 codec.AddFeedbackParam(
706 FeedbackParam(kRtcpFbParamTransportCc, kParamValueEmpty));
707 }
708
709 if (spec.info.allow_comfort_noise) {
710 // Generate a CN entry if the decoder allows it and we support the
711 // clockrate.
712 auto cn = generate_cn.find(spec.format.clockrate_hz);
713 if (cn != generate_cn.end()) {
714 cn->second = true;
715 }
716 }
717
718 // Generate a telephone-event entry if we support the clockrate.
719 auto dtmf = generate_dtmf.find(spec.format.clockrate_hz);
720 if (dtmf != generate_dtmf.end()) {
721 dtmf->second = true;
722 }
723
724 out.push_back(codec);
725
726 if (codec.name == kOpusCodecName && audio_red_for_opus_trial_enabled_) {
727 map_format({kRedCodecName, 48000, 2}, &out);
728 }
729 }
730 }
731
732 // Add CN codecs after "proper" audio codecs.
733 for (const auto& cn : generate_cn) {
734 if (cn.second) {
735 map_format({kCnCodecName, cn.first, 1}, &out);
736 }
737 }
738
739 // Add telephone-event codecs last.
740 for (const auto& dtmf : generate_dtmf) {
741 if (dtmf.second) {
742 map_format({kDtmfCodecName, dtmf.first, 1}, &out);
743 }
744 }
745
746 return out;
747}

915 // Starts the sending by setting ourselves as a sink to the AudioSource to
916 // get data callbacks.
917 // This method is called on the libjingle worker thread.

942
943 // AudioSource::Sink implementation.
944 // This method is called on the audio thread.
945 void OnData(const void* audio_data,
946 int bits_per_sample,
947 int sample_rate,
948 size_t number_of_channels,
949 size_t number_of_frames,
950 absl::optional<int64_t> absolute_capture_timestamp_ms) override {
951 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(16, bits_per_sample);
952 RTC_CHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&audio_capture_race_checker_);
953 RTC_DCHECK(stream_);
954 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::AudioFrame> audio_frame(new webrtc::AudioFrame());
955 audio_frame->UpdateFrame(
956 audio_frame->timestamp_, static_cast<const int16_t*>(audio_data),
957 number_of_frames, sample_rate, audio_frame->speech_type_,
958 audio_frame->vad_activity_, number_of_channels);
959 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10739): add dcheck that
960 // |absolute_capture_timestamp_ms| always receives a value.
961 if (absolute_capture_timestamp_ms) {
962 audio_frame->set_absolute_capture_timestamp_ms(
963 *absolute_capture_timestamp_ms);
964 }
965 stream_->SendAudioData(std::move(audio_frame));
966 }
967
968 // Callback from the |source_| when it is going away. In case Start() has
969 // never been called, this callback won't be triggered.
970 void OnClose() override {
971 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
972 // Set |source_| to nullptr to make sure no more callback will get into
973 // the source.
974 source_ = nullptr;
975 UpdateSendState();
976 }
977
978 const webrtc::RtpParameters& rtp_parameters() const {
979 return rtp_parameters_;
980 }
981
982 webrtc::RTCError SetRtpParameters(const webrtc::RtpParameters& parameters) {
983 webrtc::RTCError error = CheckRtpParametersInvalidModificationAndValues(
984 rtp_parameters_, parameters);
985 if (!error.ok()) {
986 return error;
987 }
988
989 absl::optional<int> send_rate;
990 if (audio_codec_spec_) {
991 send_rate = ComputeSendBitrate(max_send_bitrate_bps_,
992 parameters.encodings[0].max_bitrate_bps,
993 *audio_codec_spec_);
994 if (!send_rate) {
995 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR);
996 }
997 }
998
999 const absl::optional<int> old_rtp_max_bitrate =
1000 rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].max_bitrate_bps;
1001 double old_priority = rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].bitrate_priority;
1002 webrtc::Priority old_dscp = rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].network_priority;
1003 bool old_adaptive_ptime = rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].adaptive_ptime;
1004 rtp_parameters_ = parameters;
1005 config_.bitrate_priority = rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].bitrate_priority;
1006 config_.has_dscp = (rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].network_priority !=
1007 webrtc::Priority::kLow);
1008
1009 bool reconfigure_send_stream =
1010 (rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].max_bitrate_bps != old_rtp_max_bitrate) ||
1011 (rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].bitrate_priority != old_priority) ||
1012 (rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].network_priority != old_dscp) ||
1013 (rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].adaptive_ptime != old_adaptive_ptime);
1014 if (rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].max_bitrate_bps != old_rtp_max_bitrate) {
1015 // Update the bitrate range.
1016 if (send_rate) {
1017 config_.send_codec_spec->target_bitrate_bps = send_rate;
1018 }
1019 }
1020 if (reconfigure_send_stream) {
1021 // Changing adaptive_ptime may update the audio network adaptor config
1022 // used.
1023 UpdateAudioNetworkAdaptorConfig();
1024 UpdateAllowedBitrateRange();
1025 ReconfigureAudioSendStream();
1026 }
1027
1028 rtp_parameters_.rtcp.cname = config_.rtp.c_name;
1029 rtp_parameters_.rtcp.reduced_size = false;
1030
1031 // parameters.encodings[0].active could have changed.
1032 UpdateSendState();
1033 return webrtc::RTCError::OK();
1034 }
1035
1036 void SetEncoderToPacketizerFrameTransformer(
1037 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer) {
1038 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
1039 config_.frame_transformer = std::move(frame_transformer);
1040 ReconfigureAudioSendStream();
1041 }
1042
1043 private:
1044 void UpdateSendState() {
1045 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
1046 RTC_DCHECK(stream_);
1047 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(1UL, rtp_parameters_.encodings.size());
1048 if (send_ && source_ != nullptr && rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].active) {
1049 stream_->Start();
1050 } else { // !send || source_ = nullptr
1051 stream_->Stop();
1052 }
1053 }
1054
1055 void UpdateAllowedBitrateRange() {
1056 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
1057 // The order of precedence, from lowest to highest is:
1058 // - a reasonable default of 32kbps min/max
1059 // - fixed target bitrate from codec spec
1060 // - lower min bitrate if adaptive ptime is enabled
1061 // - bitrate configured in the rtp_parameter encodings settings
1062 const int kDefaultBitrateBps = 32000;
1063 config_.min_bitrate_bps = kDefaultBitrateBps;
1064 config_.max_bitrate_bps = kDefaultBitrateBps;
1065
1066 if (config_.send_codec_spec &&
1067 config_.send_codec_spec->target_bitrate_bps) {
1068 config_.min_bitrate_bps = *config_.send_codec_spec->target_bitrate_bps;
1069 config_.max_bitrate_bps = *config_.send_codec_spec->target_bitrate_bps;
1070 }
1071
1072 if (rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].adaptive_ptime) {
1073 config_.min_bitrate_bps = std::min(
1074 config_.min_bitrate_bps,
1075 static_cast<int>(adaptive_ptime_config_.min_encoder_bitrate.bps()));
1076 }
1077
1078 if (rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].min_bitrate_bps) {
1079 config_.min_bitrate_bps = *rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].min_bitrate_bps;
1080 }
1081 if (rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].max_bitrate_bps) {
1082 config_.max_bitrate_bps = *rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].max_bitrate_bps;
1083 }
1084 }
1085
1086 void UpdateSendCodecSpec(
1087 const webrtc::AudioSendStream::Config::SendCodecSpec& send_codec_spec) {
1088 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
1089 config_.send_codec_spec = send_codec_spec;
1090 auto info =
1091 config_.encoder_factory->QueryAudioEncoder(send_codec_spec.format);
1092 RTC_DCHECK(info);
1093 // If a specific target bitrate has been set for the stream, use that as
1094 // the new default bitrate when computing send bitrate.
1095 if (send_codec_spec.target_bitrate_bps) {
1096 info->default_bitrate_bps = std::max(
1097 info->min_bitrate_bps,
1098 std::min(info->max_bitrate_bps, *send_codec_spec.target_bitrate_bps));
1099 }
1100
1101 audio_codec_spec_.emplace(
1102 webrtc::AudioCodecSpec{send_codec_spec.format, *info});
1103
1104 config_.send_codec_spec->target_bitrate_bps = ComputeSendBitrate(
1105 max_send_bitrate_bps_, rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].max_bitrate_bps,
1106 *audio_codec_spec_);
1107
1108 UpdateAllowedBitrateRange();
1109
1110 // Encoder will only use two channels if the stereo parameter is set.
1111 const auto& it = send_codec_spec.format.parameters.find("stereo");
1112 if (it != send_codec_spec.format.parameters.end() && it->second == "1") {
1113 num_encoded_channels_ = 2;
1114 } else {
1115 num_encoded_channels_ = 1;
1116 }
1117 }
1118
1119 void UpdateAudioNetworkAdaptorConfig() {
1120 if (adaptive_ptime_config_.enabled ||
1121 rtp_parameters_.encodings[0].adaptive_ptime) {
1122 config_.audio_network_adaptor_config =
1123 adaptive_ptime_config_.audio_network_adaptor_config;
1124 return;
1125 }
1126 config_.audio_network_adaptor_config =
1127 audio_network_adaptor_config_from_options_;
1128 }
1129
1130 void ReconfigureAudioSendStream() {
1131 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
1132 RTC_DCHECK(stream_);
1133 stream_->Reconfigure(config_);
1134 }
1135
1136 int NumPreferredChannels() const override { return num_encoded_channels_; }
1137
1138 const AdaptivePtimeConfig adaptive_ptime_config_;
1139 webrtc::SequenceChecker worker_thread_checker_;
1140 rtc::RaceChecker audio_capture_race_checker_;
1141 webrtc::Call* call_ = nullptr;
1142 webrtc::AudioSendStream::Config config_;
1143 // The stream is owned by WebRtcAudioSendStream and may be reallocated if
1144 // configuration changes.
1145 webrtc::AudioSendStream* stream_ = nullptr;
1146
1147 // Raw pointer to AudioSource owned by LocalAudioTrackHandler.
1148 // PeerConnection will make sure invalidating the pointer before the object
1149 // goes away.
1150 AudioSource* source_ = nullptr;
1151 bool send_ = false;
1152 bool muted_ = false;
1153 int max_send_bitrate_bps_;
1154 webrtc::RtpParameters rtp_parameters_;
1155 absl::optional<webrtc::AudioCodecSpec> audio_codec_spec_;
1156 // TODO(webrtc:11717): Remove this once audio_network_adaptor in AudioOptions
1157 // has been removed.
1158 absl::optional<std::string> audio_network_adaptor_config_from_options_;
1159 std::atomic<int> num_encoded_channels_{-1};
1160};

1347 void RecreateAudioReceiveStream() {
1348 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
1349 bool was_running = false;
1350 if (stream_) {
1351 was_running = stream_->IsRunning();
1352 call_->DestroyAudioReceiveStream(stream_);
1353 }
1354 stream_ = call_->CreateAudioReceiveStream(config_);
1355 RTC_CHECK(stream_);
1356 stream_->SetGain(output_volume_);
1357 if (was_running)
1358 SetPlayout(was_running);
1359 stream_->SetSink(raw_audio_sink_.get());
1360 }

1363 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_thread_checker_);
1364 RTC_DCHECK(stream_);
1365 stream_->Reconfigure(config_);
1366 }

1371 // The stream is owned by WebRtcAudioReceiveStream and may be reallocated if
1372 // configuration changes.
1373 webrtc::AudioReceiveStream* stream_ = nullptr;
1374 float output_volume_ = 1.0;
1375 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::AudioSinkInterface> raw_audio_sink_;
1376};

1412bool WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetSendParameters(
1413 const AudioSendParameters& params) {
1414 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetSendParameters");
1415 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1416 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetSendParameters: "
1417 << params.ToString();
1418 // TODO(pthatcher): Refactor this to be more clean now that we have
1419 // all the information at once.
1420
1421 if (!SetSendCodecs(params.codecs)) {
1422 return false;
1423 }
1424
1425 if (!ValidateRtpExtensions(params.extensions)) {
1426 return false;
1427 }
1428
1429 if (ExtmapAllowMixed() != params.extmap_allow_mixed) {
1430 SetExtmapAllowMixed(params.extmap_allow_mixed);
1431 for (auto& it : send_streams_) {
1432 it.second->SetExtmapAllowMixed(params.extmap_allow_mixed);
1433 }
1434 }
1435
1436 std::vector<webrtc::RtpExtension> filtered_extensions = FilterRtpExtensions(
1437 params.extensions, webrtc::RtpExtension::IsSupportedForAudio, true,
1438 call_->trials());
1439 if (send_rtp_extensions_ != filtered_extensions) {
1440 send_rtp_extensions_.swap(filtered_extensions);
1441 for (auto& it : send_streams_) {
1442 it.second->SetRtpExtensions(send_rtp_extensions_);
1443 }
1444 }
1445 if (!params.mid.empty()) {
1446 mid_ = params.mid;
1447 for (auto& it : send_streams_) {
1448 it.second->SetMid(params.mid);
1449 }
1450 }
1451
1452 if (!SetMaxSendBitrate(params.max_bandwidth_bps)) {
1453 return false;
1454 }
1455 return SetOptions(params.options);
1456}
1457
1458bool WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetRecvParameters(
1459 const AudioRecvParameters& params) {
1460 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetRecvParameters");
1461 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1462 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetRecvParameters: "
1463 << params.ToString();
1464 // TODO(pthatcher): Refactor this to be more clean now that we have
1465 // all the information at once.
1466
1467 if (!SetRecvCodecs(params.codecs)) {
1468 return false;
1469 }
1470
1471 if (!ValidateRtpExtensions(params.extensions)) {
1472 return false;
1473 }
1474 std::vector<webrtc::RtpExtension> filtered_extensions = FilterRtpExtensions(
1475 params.extensions, webrtc::RtpExtension::IsSupportedForAudio, false,
1476 call_->trials());
1477 if (recv_rtp_extensions_ != filtered_extensions) {
1478 recv_rtp_extensions_.swap(filtered_extensions);
1479 for (auto& it : recv_streams_) {
1480 it.second->SetRtpExtensionsAndRecreateStream(recv_rtp_extensions_);
1481 }
1482 }
1483 return true;
1484}

1486webrtc::RtpParameters WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::GetRtpSendParameters(
1487 uint32_t ssrc) const {
1488 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1489 auto it = send_streams_.find(ssrc);
1490 if (it == send_streams_.end()) {
1491 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Attempting to get RTP send parameters for stream "
1492 "with ssrc "
1493 << ssrc << " which doesn't exist.";
1494 return webrtc::RtpParameters();
1495 }
1496
1497 webrtc::RtpParameters rtp_params = it->second->rtp_parameters();
1498 // Need to add the common list of codecs to the send stream-specific
1499 // RTP parameters.
1500 for (const AudioCodec& codec : send_codecs_) {
1501 rtp_params.codecs.push_back(codec.ToCodecParameters());
1502 }
1503 return rtp_params;
1504}
1505
1506webrtc::RTCError WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetRtpSendParameters(
1507 uint32_t ssrc,
1508 const webrtc::RtpParameters& parameters) {
1509 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1510 auto it = send_streams_.find(ssrc);
1511 if (it == send_streams_.end()) {
1512 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Attempting to set RTP send parameters for stream "
1513 "with ssrc "
1514 << ssrc << " which doesn't exist.";
1515 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR);
1516 }
1517
1518 // TODO(deadbeef): Handle setting parameters with a list of codecs in a
1519 // different order (which should change the send codec).
1520 webrtc::RtpParameters current_parameters = GetRtpSendParameters(ssrc);
1521 if (current_parameters.codecs != parameters.codecs) {
1522 RTC_DLOG(LS_ERROR) << "Using SetParameters to change the set of codecs "
1523 "is not currently supported.";
1524 return webrtc::RTCError(webrtc::RTCErrorType::UNSUPPORTED_PARAMETER);
1525 }
1526
1527 if (!parameters.encodings.empty()) {
1528 // Note that these values come from:
1529 // https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-tsvwg-rtcweb-qos-16#section-5
1530 rtc::DiffServCodePoint new_dscp = rtc::DSCP_DEFAULT;
1531 switch (parameters.encodings[0].network_priority) {
1532 case webrtc::Priority::kVeryLow:
1533 new_dscp = rtc::DSCP_CS1;
1534 break;
1535 case webrtc::Priority::kLow:
1536 new_dscp = rtc::DSCP_DEFAULT;
1537 break;
1538 case webrtc::Priority::kMedium:
1539 new_dscp = rtc::DSCP_EF;
1540 break;
1541 case webrtc::Priority::kHigh:
1542 new_dscp = rtc::DSCP_EF;
1543 break;
1544 }
1545 SetPreferredDscp(new_dscp);
1546 }
1547
1548 // TODO(minyue): The following legacy actions go into
1549 // |WebRtcAudioSendStream::SetRtpParameters()| which is called at the end,
1550 // though there are two difference:
1551 // 1. |WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetChannelSendParameters()| only calls
1552 // |SetSendCodec| while |WebRtcAudioSendStream::SetRtpParameters()| calls
1553 // |SetSendCodecs|. The outcome should be the same.
1554 // 2. AudioSendStream can be recreated.
1555
1556 // Codecs are handled at the WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel level.
1557 webrtc::RtpParameters reduced_params = parameters;
1558 reduced_params.codecs.clear();
1559 return it->second->SetRtpParameters(reduced_params);
1560}

1562webrtc::RtpParameters WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::GetRtpReceiveParameters(
1563 uint32_t ssrc) const {
1564 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1565 webrtc::RtpParameters rtp_params;
1566 auto it = recv_streams_.find(ssrc);
1567 if (it == recv_streams_.end()) {
1568 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
1569 << "Attempting to get RTP receive parameters for stream "
1570 "with ssrc "
1571 << ssrc << " which doesn't exist.";
1572 return webrtc::RtpParameters();
1573 }
1574 rtp_params = it->second->GetRtpParameters();
1575
1576 for (const AudioCodec& codec : recv_codecs_) {
1577 rtp_params.codecs.push_back(codec.ToCodecParameters());

1600bool WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetOptions(const AudioOptions& options) {
1601 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1602 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Setting voice channel options: " << options.ToString();
1603
1604 // We retain all of the existing options, and apply the given ones
1605 // on top. This means there is no way to "clear" options such that
1606 // they go back to the engine default.
1607 options_.SetAll(options);
1608 if (!engine()->ApplyOptions(options_)) {
1609 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
1610 << "Failed to apply engine options during channel SetOptions.";
1611 return false;
1612 }
1613
1614 absl::optional<std::string> audio_network_adaptor_config =
1615 GetAudioNetworkAdaptorConfig(options_);
1616 for (auto& it : send_streams_) {
1617 it.second->SetAudioNetworkAdaptorConfig(audio_network_adaptor_config);
1618 }
1619
1620 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Set voice channel options. Current options: "
1621 << options_.ToString();
1622 return true;
1623}
1624
1625bool WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetRecvCodecs(
1626 const std::vector<AudioCodec>& codecs) {
1627 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1628
1629 // Set the payload types to be used for incoming media.
1630 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Setting receive voice codecs.";
1631
1632 if (!VerifyUniquePayloadTypes(codecs)) {
1633 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Codec payload types overlap.";
1634 return false;
1635 }
1636
1637 // Create a payload type -> SdpAudioFormat map with all the decoders. Fail
1638 // unless the factory claims to support all decoders.
1639 std::map<int, webrtc::SdpAudioFormat> decoder_map;
1640 for (const AudioCodec& codec : codecs) {
1641 // Log a warning if a codec's payload type is changing. This used to be
1642 // treated as an error. It's abnormal, but not really illegal.
1643 AudioCodec old_codec;
1644 if (FindCodec(recv_codecs_, codec, &old_codec) &&
1645 old_codec.id != codec.id) {
1646 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << codec.name << " mapped to a second payload type ("
1647 << codec.id << ", was already mapped to "
1648 << old_codec.id << ")";
1649 }
1650 auto format = AudioCodecToSdpAudioFormat(codec);
1651 if (!IsCodec(codec, kCnCodecName) && !IsCodec(codec, kDtmfCodecName) &&
1652 (!audio_red_for_opus_trial_enabled_ ||
1653 !IsCodec(codec, kRedCodecName)) &&
1654 !engine()->decoder_factory_->IsSupportedDecoder(format)) {
1655 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Unsupported codec: " << rtc::ToString(format);
1656 return false;
1657 }
1658 // We allow adding new codecs but don't allow changing the payload type of
1659 // codecs that are already configured since we might already be receiving
1660 // packets with that payload type. See RFC3264, Section 8.3.2.
1661 // TODO(deadbeef): Also need to check for clashes with previously mapped
1662 // payload types, and not just currently mapped ones. For example, this
1663 // should be illegal:
1664 // 1. {100: opus/48000/2, 101: ISAC/16000}
1665 // 2. {100: opus/48000/2}
1666 // 3. {100: opus/48000/2, 101: ISAC/32000}
1667 // Though this check really should happen at a higher level, since this
1668 // conflict could happen between audio and video codecs.
1669 auto existing = decoder_map_.find(codec.id);
1670 if (existing != decoder_map_.end() && !existing->second.Matches(format)) {
1671 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Attempting to use payload type " << codec.id
1672 << " for " << codec.name
1673 << ", but it is already used for "
1674 << existing->second.name;
1675 return false;
1676 }
1677 decoder_map.insert({codec.id, std::move(format)});
1678 }
1679
1680 if (decoder_map == decoder_map_) {
1681 // There's nothing new to configure.
1682 return true;
1683 }
1684
1685 bool playout_enabled = playout_;
1686 // Receive codecs can not be changed while playing. So we temporarily
1687 // pause playout.
1688 SetPlayout(false);
1689 RTC_DCHECK(!playout_);
1690
1691 decoder_map_ = std::move(decoder_map);
1692 for (auto& kv : recv_streams_) {
1693 kv.second->SetDecoderMap(decoder_map_);
1694 }
1695
1696 recv_codecs_ = codecs;
1697
1698 SetPlayout(playout_enabled);
1699 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(playout_, playout_enabled);
1700
1701 return true;
1702}
1703
1704// Utility function called from SetSendParameters() to extract current send
1705// codec settings from the given list of codecs (originally from SDP). Both send
1706// and receive streams may be reconfigured based on the new settings.
1707bool WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetSendCodecs(
1708 const std::vector<AudioCodec>& codecs) {
1709 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1710 dtmf_payload_type_ = absl::nullopt;
1711 dtmf_payload_freq_ = -1;
1712
1713 // Validate supplied codecs list.
1714 for (const AudioCodec& codec : codecs) {
1715 // TODO(solenberg): Validate more aspects of input - that payload types
1716 // don't overlap, remove redundant/unsupported codecs etc -
1717 // the same way it is done for RtpHeaderExtensions.
1718 if (codec.id < kMinPayloadType || codec.id > kMaxPayloadType) {
1719 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Codec payload type out of range: "
1720 << ToString(codec);
1721 return false;
1722 }
1723 }
1724
1725 // Find PT of telephone-event codec with lowest clockrate, as a fallback, in
1726 // case we don't have a DTMF codec with a rate matching the send codec's, or
1727 // if this function returns early.
1728 std::vector<AudioCodec> dtmf_codecs;
1729 for (const AudioCodec& codec : codecs) {
1730 if (IsCodec(codec, kDtmfCodecName)) {
1731 dtmf_codecs.push_back(codec);
1732 if (!dtmf_payload_type_ || codec.clockrate < dtmf_payload_freq_) {
1733 dtmf_payload_type_ = codec.id;
1734 dtmf_payload_freq_ = codec.clockrate;
1735 }
1736 }
1737 }
1738
1739 // Scan through the list to figure out the codec to use for sending.
1740 absl::optional<webrtc::AudioSendStream::Config::SendCodecSpec>
1741 send_codec_spec;
1742 webrtc::BitrateConstraints bitrate_config;
1743 absl::optional<webrtc::AudioCodecInfo> voice_codec_info;
1744 size_t send_codec_position = 0;
1745 for (const AudioCodec& voice_codec : codecs) {
1746 if (!(IsCodec(voice_codec, kCnCodecName) ||
1747 IsCodec(voice_codec, kDtmfCodecName) ||
1748 IsCodec(voice_codec, kRedCodecName))) {
1749 webrtc::SdpAudioFormat format(voice_codec.name, voice_codec.clockrate,
1750 voice_codec.channels, voice_codec.params);
1751
1752 voice_codec_info = engine()->encoder_factory_->QueryAudioEncoder(format);
1753 if (!voice_codec_info) {
1754 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unknown codec " << ToString(voice_codec);
1755 continue;
1756 }
1757
1758 send_codec_spec = webrtc::AudioSendStream::Config::SendCodecSpec(
1759 voice_codec.id, format);
1760 if (voice_codec.bitrate > 0) {
1761 send_codec_spec->target_bitrate_bps = voice_codec.bitrate;
1762 }
1763 send_codec_spec->transport_cc_enabled = HasTransportCc(voice_codec);
1764 send_codec_spec->nack_enabled = HasNack(voice_codec);
1765 bitrate_config = GetBitrateConfigForCodec(voice_codec);
1766 break;
1767 }
1768 send_codec_position++;
1769 }
1770
1771 if (!send_codec_spec) {
1772 return false;
1773 }
1774
1775 RTC_DCHECK(voice_codec_info);
1776 if (voice_codec_info->allow_comfort_noise) {
1777 // Loop through the codecs list again to find the CN codec.
1778 // TODO(solenberg): Break out into a separate function?
1779 for (const AudioCodec& cn_codec : codecs) {
1780 if (IsCodec(cn_codec, kCnCodecName) &&
1781 cn_codec.clockrate == send_codec_spec->format.clockrate_hz &&
1782 cn_codec.channels == voice_codec_info->num_channels) {
1783 if (cn_codec.channels != 1) {
1784 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
1785 << "CN #channels " << cn_codec.channels << " not supported.";
1786 } else if (cn_codec.clockrate != 8000 && cn_codec.clockrate != 16000 &&
1787 cn_codec.clockrate != 32000) {
1788 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
1789 << "CN frequency " << cn_codec.clockrate << " not supported.";
1790 } else {
1791 send_codec_spec->cng_payload_type = cn_codec.id;
1792 }
1793 break;
1794 }
1795 }
1796
1797 // Find the telephone-event PT exactly matching the preferred send codec.
1798 for (const AudioCodec& dtmf_codec : dtmf_codecs) {
1799 if (dtmf_codec.clockrate == send_codec_spec->format.clockrate_hz) {
1800 dtmf_payload_type_ = dtmf_codec.id;
1801 dtmf_payload_freq_ = dtmf_codec.clockrate;
1802 break;
1803 }
1804 }
1805 }
1806
1807 if (audio_red_for_opus_trial_enabled_) {
1808 // Loop through the codecs to find the RED codec that matches opus
1809 // with respect to clockrate and number of channels.
1810 size_t red_codec_position = 0;
1811 for (const AudioCodec& red_codec : codecs) {
1812 if (red_codec_position < send_codec_position &&
1813 IsCodec(red_codec, kRedCodecName) &&
1814 red_codec.clockrate == send_codec_spec->format.clockrate_hz &&
1815 red_codec.channels == send_codec_spec->format.num_channels) {
1816 send_codec_spec->red_payload_type = red_codec.id;
1817 break;
1818 }
1819 red_codec_position++;
1820 }
1821 }
1822
1823 if (send_codec_spec_ != send_codec_spec) {
1824 send_codec_spec_ = std::move(send_codec_spec);
1825 // Apply new settings to all streams.
1826 for (const auto& kv : send_streams_) {
1827 kv.second->SetSendCodecSpec(*send_codec_spec_);
1828 }
1829 } else {
1830 // If the codec isn't changing, set the start bitrate to -1 which means
1831 // "unchanged" so that BWE isn't affected.
1832 bitrate_config.start_bitrate_bps = -1;
1833 }
1834 call_->GetTransportControllerSend()->SetSdpBitrateParameters(bitrate_config);
1835
1836 // Check if the transport cc feedback or NACK status has changed on the
1837 // preferred send codec, and in that case reconfigure all receive streams.
1838 if (recv_transport_cc_enabled_ != send_codec_spec_->transport_cc_enabled ||
1839 recv_nack_enabled_ != send_codec_spec_->nack_enabled) {
1840 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Recreate all the receive streams because the send "
1841 "codec has changed.";
1842 recv_transport_cc_enabled_ = send_codec_spec_->transport_cc_enabled;
1843 recv_nack_enabled_ = send_codec_spec_->nack_enabled;
1844 for (auto& kv : recv_streams_) {
1845 kv.second->SetUseTransportCcAndRecreateStream(recv_transport_cc_enabled_,
1846 recv_nack_enabled_);
1847 }
1848 }
1849
1850 send_codecs_ = codecs;
1851 return true;
1852}

1854void WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetPlayout(bool playout) {
1855 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetPlayout");
1856 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1857 if (playout_ == playout) {
1858 return;
1859 }
1860
1861 for (const auto& kv : recv_streams_) {
1862 kv.second->SetPlayout(playout);
1863 }
1864 playout_ = playout;

1867void WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetSend(bool send) {
1868 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetSend");
1869 if (send_ == send) {
1870 return;
1871 }
1872
1873 // Apply channel specific options, and initialize the ADM for recording (this
1874 // may take time on some platforms, e.g. Android).
1875 if (send) {
1876 engine()->ApplyOptions(options_);
1877
1878 // InitRecording() may return an error if the ADM is already recording.
1879 if (!engine()->adm()->RecordingIsInitialized() &&
1880 !engine()->adm()->Recording()) {
1881 if (engine()->adm()->InitRecording() != 0) {
1882 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to initialize recording";
1883 }
1884 }
1885 }
1886
1887 // Change the settings on each send channel.
1888 for (auto& kv : send_streams_) {
1889 kv.second->SetSend(send);
1890 }
1891
1892 send_ = send;
1893}

1896 bool enable,

1898 AudioSource* source) {

1903 return false;

1914bool WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::AddSendStream(const StreamParams& sp) {
1915 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::AddSendStream");
1916 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1917 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "AddSendStream: " << sp.ToString();
1918
1919 uint32_t ssrc = sp.first_ssrc();
1920 RTC_DCHECK(0 != ssrc);
1921
1922 if (send_streams_.find(ssrc) != send_streams_.end()) {
1923 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Stream already exists with ssrc " << ssrc;
1924 return false;
1925 }
1926
1927 absl::optional<std::string> audio_network_adaptor_config =
1928 GetAudioNetworkAdaptorConfig(options_);
1929 WebRtcAudioSendStream* stream = new WebRtcAudioSendStream(
1930 ssrc, mid_, sp.cname, sp.id, send_codec_spec_, ExtmapAllowMixed(),
1931 send_rtp_extensions_, max_send_bitrate_bps_,
1932 audio_config_.rtcp_report_interval_ms, audio_network_adaptor_config,
1933 call_, this, engine()->encoder_factory_, codec_pair_id_, nullptr,
1934 crypto_options_);
1935 send_streams_.insert(std::make_pair(ssrc, stream));
1936
1937 // At this point the stream's local SSRC has been updated. If it is the first
1938 // send stream, make sure that all the receive streams are updated with the
1939 // same SSRC in order to send receiver reports.
1940 if (send_streams_.size() == 1) {
1941 receiver_reports_ssrc_ = ssrc;
1942 for (const auto& kv : recv_streams_) {
1943 // TODO(solenberg): Allow applications to set the RTCP SSRC of receive
1944 // streams instead, so we can avoid reconfiguring the streams here.
1945 kv.second->SetLocalSsrc(ssrc);
1946 }
1947 }
1948
1949 send_streams_[ssrc]->SetSend(send_);
1950 return true;
1951}

1953bool WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::RemoveSendStream(uint32_t ssrc) {
1954 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::RemoveSendStream");
1955 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1956 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "RemoveSendStream: " << ssrc;
1957
1958 auto it = send_streams_.find(ssrc);
1959 if (it == send_streams_.end()) {
1960 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Try to remove stream with ssrc " << ssrc
1961 << " which doesn't exist.";
1962 return false;
1963 }
1964
1965 it->second->SetSend(false);
1966
1967 // TODO(solenberg): If we're removing the receiver_reports_ssrc_ stream, find
1968 // the first active send stream and use that instead, reassociating receive
1969 // streams.
1970
1971 delete it->second;
1972 send_streams_.erase(it);
1973 if (send_streams_.empty()) {
1974 SetSend(false);
1975 }
1976 return true;
1977}

1979bool WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::AddRecvStream(const StreamParams& sp) {
1980 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::AddRecvStream");
1981 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1982 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "AddRecvStream: " << sp.ToString();
1983
1984 if (!sp.has_ssrcs()) {
1985 // This is a StreamParam with unsignaled SSRCs. Store it, so it can be used
1986 // later when we know the SSRCs on the first packet arrival.
1987 unsignaled_stream_params_ = sp;
1988 return true;
1989 }
1990
1991 if (!ValidateStreamParams(sp)) {
1992 return false;
1993 }
1994
1995 const uint32_t ssrc = sp.first_ssrc();
1996
1997 // If this stream was previously received unsignaled, we promote it, possibly
1998 // recreating the AudioReceiveStream, if stream ids have changed.
1999 if (MaybeDeregisterUnsignaledRecvStream(ssrc)) {
2000 recv_streams_[ssrc]->MaybeRecreateAudioReceiveStream(sp.stream_ids());
2001 return true;
2002 }
2003
2004 if (recv_streams_.find(ssrc) != recv_streams_.end()) {
2005 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Stream already exists with ssrc " << ssrc;
2006 return false;
2007 }
2008
2009 // Create a new channel for receiving audio data.
2010 recv_streams_.insert(std::make_pair(
2011 ssrc, new WebRtcAudioReceiveStream(
2012 ssrc, receiver_reports_ssrc_, recv_transport_cc_enabled_,
2013 recv_nack_enabled_, sp.stream_ids(), recv_rtp_extensions_,
2014 call_, this, engine()->decoder_factory_, decoder_map_,
2015 codec_pair_id_, engine()->audio_jitter_buffer_max_packets_,
2016 engine()->audio_jitter_buffer_fast_accelerate_,
2017 engine()->audio_jitter_buffer_min_delay_ms_,
2018 engine()->audio_jitter_buffer_enable_rtx_handling_,
2019 unsignaled_frame_decryptor_, crypto_options_, nullptr)));
2020 recv_streams_[ssrc]->SetPlayout(playout_);
2021
2022 return true;
2023}

2025bool WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::RemoveRecvStream(uint32_t ssrc) {
2026 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::RemoveRecvStream");
2027 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
2028 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "RemoveRecvStream: " << ssrc;
2029

2032 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Try to remove stream with ssrc " << ssrc

2209
2210void WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::OnPacketReceived(rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer packet,
2211 int64_t packet_time_us) {
2212 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&network_thread_checker_);
2213 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): This code is very similar to what
2214 // WebRtcVideoChannel::OnPacketReceived does. For maintainability and
2215 // consistency it would be good to move the interaction with call_->Receiver()
2216 // to a common implementation and provide a callback on the worker thread
2217 // for the exception case (DELIVERY_UNKNOWN_SSRC) and how retry is attempted.
2218 worker_thread_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(task_safety_, [this, packet,
2219 packet_time_us] {
2220 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
2221
2222 webrtc::PacketReceiver::DeliveryStatus delivery_result =
2223 call_->Receiver()->DeliverPacket(webrtc::MediaType::AUDIO, packet,
2224 packet_time_us);
2225
2226 if (delivery_result != webrtc::PacketReceiver::DELIVERY_UNKNOWN_SSRC) {
2227 return;
2228 }
2229
2230 // Create an unsignaled receive stream for this previously not received
2231 // ssrc. If there already is N unsignaled receive streams, delete the
2232 // oldest. See: https://bugs.chromium.org/p/webrtc/issues/detail?id=5208
2233 uint32_t ssrc = 0;
2234 if (!GetRtpSsrc(packet.cdata(), packet.size(), &ssrc)) {
2235 return;
2236 }
2237 RTC_DCHECK(!absl::c_linear_search(unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_, ssrc));
2238
2239 // Add new stream.
2240 StreamParams sp = unsignaled_stream_params_;
2241 sp.ssrcs.push_back(ssrc);
2242 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Creating unsignaled receive stream for SSRC=" << ssrc;
2243 if (!AddRecvStream(sp)) {
2244 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Could not create unsignaled receive stream.";
2245 return;
2246 }
2247 unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_.push_back(ssrc);
2248 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_LINEAR("WebRTC.Audio.NumOfUnsignaledStreams",
2249 unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_.size(), 1, 100, 101);
2250
2251 // Remove oldest unsignaled stream, if we have too many.
2252 if (unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_.size() > kMaxUnsignaledRecvStreams) {
2253 uint32_t remove_ssrc = unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_.front();
2254 RTC_DLOG(LS_INFO) << "Removing unsignaled receive stream with SSRC="
2255 << remove_ssrc;
2256 RemoveRecvStream(remove_ssrc);
2257 }
2258 RTC_DCHECK_GE(kMaxUnsignaledRecvStreams, unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_.size());
2259
2260 SetOutputVolume(ssrc, default_recv_volume_);
2261 SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(ssrc, default_recv_base_minimum_delay_ms_);
2262
2263 // The default sink can only be attached to one stream at a time, so we hook
2264 // it up to the *latest* unsignaled stream we've seen, in order to support
2265 // the case where the SSRC of one unsignaled stream changes.
2266 if (default_sink_) {
2267 for (uint32_t drop_ssrc : unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_) {
2268 auto it = recv_streams_.find(drop_ssrc);
2269 it->second->SetRawAudioSink(nullptr);
2270 }
2271 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::AudioSinkInterface> proxy_sink(
2272 new ProxySink(default_sink_.get()));
2273 SetRawAudioSink(ssrc, std::move(proxy_sink));
2274 }
2275
2276 delivery_result = call_->Receiver()->DeliverPacket(webrtc::MediaType::AUDIO,
2277 packet, packet_time_us);
2278 RTC_DCHECK_NE(webrtc::PacketReceiver::DELIVERY_UNKNOWN_SSRC,
2279 delivery_result);
2280 }));
2281}

2285 // TODO(tommi): We shouldn't need to go through call_ to deliver this

2288 // So we should be able to remove OnSentPacket from Call and handle this per

2308bool WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::MuteStream(uint32_t ssrc, bool muted) {
2309 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);

2311 if (it == send_streams_.end()) {

2313 return false;

2315 it->second->SetMuted(muted);
2316
2317 // TODO(solenberg):
2318 // We set the AGC to mute state only when all the channels are muted.
2319 // This implementation is not ideal, instead we should signal the AGC when
2320 // the mic channel is muted/unmuted. We can't do it today because there
2321 // is no good way to know which stream is mapping to the mic channel.
2322 bool all_muted = muted;
2323 for (const auto& kv : send_streams_) {
2324 all_muted = all_muted && kv.second->muted();
2325 }
2326 webrtc::AudioProcessing* ap = engine()->apm();
2327 if (ap) {
2328 ap->set_output_will_be_muted(all_muted);
2329 }
2330

2353
2354bool WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::GetStats(VoiceMediaInfo* info,
2355 bool get_and_clear_legacy_stats) {
2356 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::GetStats");
2357 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
2358 RTC_DCHECK(info);
2359
2360 // Get SSRC and stats for each sender.
2361 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(info->senders.size(), 0U);
2362 for (const auto& stream : send_streams_) {
2363 webrtc::AudioSendStream::Stats stats =
2364 stream.second->GetStats(recv_streams_.size() > 0);
2365 VoiceSenderInfo sinfo;
2366 sinfo.add_ssrc(stats.local_ssrc);
2367 sinfo.payload_bytes_sent = stats.payload_bytes_sent;
2368 sinfo.header_and_padding_bytes_sent = stats.header_and_padding_bytes_sent;
2369 sinfo.retransmitted_bytes_sent = stats.retransmitted_bytes_sent;
2370 sinfo.packets_sent = stats.packets_sent;
2371 sinfo.retransmitted_packets_sent = stats.retransmitted_packets_sent;
2372 sinfo.packets_lost = stats.packets_lost;
2373 sinfo.fraction_lost = stats.fraction_lost;
2374 sinfo.codec_name = stats.codec_name;
2375 sinfo.codec_payload_type = stats.codec_payload_type;
2376 sinfo.jitter_ms = stats.jitter_ms;
2377 sinfo.rtt_ms = stats.rtt_ms;
2378 sinfo.audio_level = stats.audio_level;
2379 sinfo.total_input_energy = stats.total_input_energy;
2380 sinfo.total_input_duration = stats.total_input_duration;
2381 sinfo.typing_noise_detected = (send_ ? stats.typing_noise_detected : false);
2382 sinfo.ana_statistics = stats.ana_statistics;
2383 sinfo.apm_statistics = stats.apm_statistics;
2384 sinfo.report_block_datas = std::move(stats.report_block_datas);
2385 info->senders.push_back(sinfo);
2386 }
2387
2388 // Get SSRC and stats for each receiver.
2389 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(info->receivers.size(), 0U);
2390 for (const auto& stream : recv_streams_) {
2391 uint32_t ssrc = stream.first;
2392 // When SSRCs are unsignaled, there's only one audio MediaStreamTrack, but
2393 // multiple RTP streams can be received over time (if the SSRC changes for
2394 // whatever reason). We only want the RTCMediaStreamTrackStats to represent
2395 // the stats for the most recent stream (the one whose audio is actually
2396 // routed to the MediaStreamTrack), so here we ignore any unsignaled SSRCs
2397 // except for the most recent one (last in the vector). This is somewhat of
2398 // a hack, and means you don't get *any* stats for these inactive streams,
2399 // but it's slightly better than the previous behavior, which was "highest
2400 // SSRC wins".
2401 // See: https://bugs.chromium.org/p/webrtc/issues/detail?id=8158
2402 if (!unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_.empty()) {
2403 auto end_it = --unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_.end();
2404 if (absl::linear_search(unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_.begin(), end_it, ssrc)) {
2405 continue;
2406 }
2407 }
2408 webrtc::AudioReceiveStream::Stats stats =
2409 stream.second->GetStats(get_and_clear_legacy_stats);
2410 VoiceReceiverInfo rinfo;
2411 rinfo.add_ssrc(stats.remote_ssrc);
2412 rinfo.payload_bytes_rcvd = stats.payload_bytes_rcvd;
2413 rinfo.header_and_padding_bytes_rcvd = stats.header_and_padding_bytes_rcvd;
2414 rinfo.packets_rcvd = stats.packets_rcvd;
2415 rinfo.fec_packets_received = stats.fec_packets_received;
2416 rinfo.fec_packets_discarded = stats.fec_packets_discarded;
2417 rinfo.packets_lost = stats.packets_lost;
2418 rinfo.codec_name = stats.codec_name;
2419 rinfo.codec_payload_type = stats.codec_payload_type;
2420 rinfo.jitter_ms = stats.jitter_ms;
2421 rinfo.jitter_buffer_ms = stats.jitter_buffer_ms;
2422 rinfo.jitter_buffer_preferred_ms = stats.jitter_buffer_preferred_ms;
2423 rinfo.delay_estimate_ms = stats.delay_estimate_ms;
2424 rinfo.audio_level = stats.audio_level;
2425 rinfo.total_output_energy = stats.total_output_energy;
2426 rinfo.total_samples_received = stats.total_samples_received;
2427 rinfo.total_output_duration = stats.total_output_duration;
2428 rinfo.concealed_samples = stats.concealed_samples;
2429 rinfo.silent_concealed_samples = stats.silent_concealed_samples;
2430 rinfo.concealment_events = stats.concealment_events;
2431 rinfo.jitter_buffer_delay_seconds = stats.jitter_buffer_delay_seconds;
2432 rinfo.jitter_buffer_emitted_count = stats.jitter_buffer_emitted_count;
2433 rinfo.jitter_buffer_target_delay_seconds =
2434 stats.jitter_buffer_target_delay_seconds;
2435 rinfo.inserted_samples_for_deceleration =
2436 stats.inserted_samples_for_deceleration;
2437 rinfo.removed_samples_for_acceleration =
2438 stats.removed_samples_for_acceleration;
2439 rinfo.expand_rate = stats.expand_rate;
2440 rinfo.speech_expand_rate = stats.speech_expand_rate;
2441 rinfo.secondary_decoded_rate = stats.secondary_decoded_rate;
2442 rinfo.secondary_discarded_rate = stats.secondary_discarded_rate;
2443 rinfo.accelerate_rate = stats.accelerate_rate;
2444 rinfo.preemptive_expand_rate = stats.preemptive_expand_rate;
2445 rinfo.delayed_packet_outage_samples = stats.delayed_packet_outage_samples;
2446 rinfo.decoding_calls_to_silence_generator =
2447 stats.decoding_calls_to_silence_generator;
2448 rinfo.decoding_calls_to_neteq = stats.decoding_calls_to_neteq;
2449 rinfo.decoding_normal = stats.decoding_normal;
2450 rinfo.decoding_plc = stats.decoding_plc;
2451 rinfo.decoding_codec_plc = stats.decoding_codec_plc;
2452 rinfo.decoding_cng = stats.decoding_cng;
2453 rinfo.decoding_plc_cng = stats.decoding_plc_cng;
2454 rinfo.decoding_muted_output = stats.decoding_muted_output;
2455 rinfo.capture_start_ntp_time_ms = stats.capture_start_ntp_time_ms;
2456 rinfo.last_packet_received_timestamp_ms =
2457 stats.last_packet_received_timestamp_ms;
2458 rinfo.estimated_playout_ntp_timestamp_ms =
2459 stats.estimated_playout_ntp_timestamp_ms;
2460 rinfo.jitter_buffer_flushes = stats.jitter_buffer_flushes;
2461 rinfo.relative_packet_arrival_delay_seconds =
2462 stats.relative_packet_arrival_delay_seconds;
2463 rinfo.interruption_count = stats.interruption_count;
2464 rinfo.total_interruption_duration_ms = stats.total_interruption_duration_ms;
2465 rinfo.last_sender_report_timestamp_ms =
2466 stats.last_sender_report_timestamp_ms;
2467 rinfo.last_sender_report_remote_timestamp_ms =
2468 stats.last_sender_report_remote_timestamp_ms;
2469 rinfo.sender_reports_packets_sent = stats.sender_reports_packets_sent;
2470 rinfo.sender_reports_bytes_sent = stats.sender_reports_bytes_sent;
2471 rinfo.sender_reports_reports_count = stats.sender_reports_reports_count;
2472
2473 info->receivers.push_back(rinfo);
2474 }
2475
2476 // Get codec info
2477 for (const AudioCodec& codec : send_codecs_) {
2478 webrtc::RtpCodecParameters codec_params = codec.ToCodecParameters();
2479 info->send_codecs.insert(
2480 std::make_pair(codec_params.payload_type, std::move(codec_params)));
2481 }
2482 for (const AudioCodec& codec : recv_codecs_) {
2483 webrtc::RtpCodecParameters codec_params = codec.ToCodecParameters();
2484 info->receive_codecs.insert(
2485 std::make_pair(codec_params.payload_type, std::move(codec_params)));
2486 }
2487 info->device_underrun_count = engine_->adm()->GetPlayoutUnderrunCount();
2488
2489 return true;
2490}

2492void WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetRawAudioSink(
2493 uint32_t ssrc,
2494 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::AudioSinkInterface> sink) {
2495 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
2496 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetRawAudioSink: ssrc:"
2497 << ssrc << " " << (sink ? "(ptr)" : "NULL");
2498 const auto it = recv_streams_.find(ssrc);
2499 if (it == recv_streams_.end()) {
2500 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "SetRawAudioSink: no recv stream " << ssrc;
2501 return;
2502 }
2503 it->second->SetRawAudioSink(std::move(sink));
2504}
2505
2506void WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetDefaultRawAudioSink(
2507 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::AudioSinkInterface> sink) {
2508 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
2509 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::SetDefaultRawAudioSink:";
2510 if (!unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_.empty()) {
2511 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::AudioSinkInterface> proxy_sink(
2512 sink ? new ProxySink(sink.get()) : nullptr);
2513 SetRawAudioSink(unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_.back(), std::move(proxy_sink));
2514 }
2515 default_sink_ = std::move(sink);
2516}

2569bool WebRtcVoiceMediaChannel::MaybeDeregisterUnsignaledRecvStream(
2570 uint32_t ssrc) {
2571 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
2572 auto it = absl::c_find(unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_, ssrc);
2573 if (it != unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_.end()) {
2574 unsignaled_recv_ssrcs_.erase(it);
2575 return true;
2576 }
2577 return false;
